{
  "texts": [
    "Nephrologists typically use KUB X-ray images to identify kidney stones.",
    "This information helps determine whether the individual is healthy or a patient requiring treatment.",
    "Directing an X-ray beam through the body obtains a KUB radiograph.",
    "The resulting image appears in shades of black and white, depending on the varying densities and X-ray absorption of different body parts.",
    "Muscles and fat appear grey due to medium densities, while bones appear white due to their high density."
  ]
}